  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Expansion of CRAFT &amp; Fairmined in Honduras</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Artisanal and small-scale mining (ASM) is an invisible sector in Honduras, as there is a lack of greater recognition of its current contributions and needs. The creation of the Unit for ASM in INHGEOMIN (the country&apos;s mining authority) has greatly benefited in the accompaniment and incidence in the ASM sector. However, the number of institutional officials and technical knowledge are not yet sufficient to serve the entire ASM population and its demands. Also, the ASM sector is poorly recognised in the market leading to lack of formal market access. Minas y Cuevas (the projects&apos; pioneering mining cooperative) already complies with CRAFT as of december 2019, guaranteeing that it can access formal markets, as long as it continues improvements. The project seeks to build on this foundation and to encourage the adoption of best mining practices in the Artisanal and Small-scale Mining (ASM) sector in Honduras, to become a legitimate, responsible and profitable sector that promotes inclusive and sustainable development in rural areas, improving the quality of life of miners and their communities. Market access will be facilitated through selling CRAFT and Fairmined gold from Honduras and European downstream actors. Indeed, Heimerle und Meule (a German refiner) and Samlerhuset (mint of Norway) are full partners of the project and committed to source from ASM in Honduras.</narrative>
  </description>
